727372f-b.text:
A general view northwestward from Maurice Ave. and 65th Street, showing the area between the Woodside Brewery (right) and Mt. 2ion Cemetery (left). To the left center appears the Thomas H. Betts farmhouse (clothesline suspended therefromA of 1852 which at a later
date was known as Erb's.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727374f-a.text:
Maurice Ave., north side, at 65th Street, showing a frame house at the N.W. corner. In the background appears that area between Queens Boulevard (right) and Mt. 2ion Cemetery (left) with the Woodside Brewery prominent on the horizon. At the left is the Thomas H. Betts farmhouse of 1852 (clothesline suspended therefrom).
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
